      • checkTimeout

        private static boolean checkTimeout(NumberWrapper timeoutUntil,
                                    NumberWrapper stepDuration)
        Check whether the timeout period has elapsed. If it has, return true and update the timeout. Otherwise, return false.
        Parameters:
        timeoutUntil - The system time (in milliseconds) that indicates the timeout is done.
        stepDuration - The duration of the next timeout in milliseconds. For example, a stepDuration of 1000 means checkTimeout will return true if called after 1 second has elapsed.
        Returns:
        True if the timeout is done. Otherwise return false.
